// PAGE BUILDER — ADMIN META BOX + FRONTEND RENDERING
// ============================================================================
//
// WHY: The society admin needs to build pages by arranging pre-built widgets
//      without ever touching the WordPress block editor. Gutenberg is too
//      complex for octogenarians. This gives them a dead-simple interface:
//      pick a widget, configure it, arrange with up/down arrows, hit Save.
//
// HOW IT WORKS:
//      1. theme_page_templates filter — adds "SocietyPress Builder" to the
//         template dropdown in the Page editor
//      2. add_meta_boxes — shows the builder meta box on pages using that
//         template (Gutenberg is disabled, classic editor is hidden)
//      3. save_post_page — saves widget configuration to post meta
//      4. template_include — on the frontend, renders widgets in order
//
// DATA STORAGE:
//      Widget config stored as page post_meta (_sp_page_widgets):
//      [
//          [ 'type' => 'rich_text', 'settings' => [ 'content' => '...' ] ],
//          [ 'type' => 'heading',   'settings' => [ 'text' => '...' ] ],
//      ]
//
// WIDGET TYPES:
//      Content:  rich_text, member_directory, surname_lookup, membership_tiers
//      Info:     contact_card, member_stats, heading, image
//      Actions:  button, contact_form
// ============================================================================


